snippet.textDisplay:
costumes and singing and idea and everything is 10/10. probably the best set design in any coke studio ever.
my only gripe is that the 1st transition was too abrupt.. and not smooth and seamless, background music should have been prolonged into the Meghdol vocals for continuity purposes (like it was in the 2nd transition).
but the ending man, it was perfect.

well I m not a musician but from listeners POV: Transitions of the sound didn't blend.. it feels bit off suddenly in the middle.. so mixing & mastering this masterpiece should be well planned for smooth vibe

the cinematography on that girl felt less. apart from that, it's enchanting!

snippet.textDisplay:
Sorry....For the very first time, I couldn't like a song from Coke Studio Bangla. At all. Apart from that female singer, nothing is natural here, rather highly artificial and imposed. Desperate and failed attempt to represent village culture, folklore by some city people.

That girl pretending to be Bonbibi in the background, seemed hilarious. The make-up artist had no idea that this song is about Bonbibi of Bangladesh, not Hawaiian or Caribbean Bonbibi. 

I feel like this song will be one of the lowest viewed songs, if not the lowest, of Coke studio Bangla.
